This naturally reduces the efficiency of sales

08:58.000 --> 09:03.000
And that square where the buyer is only 30%

09:03.000 --> 09:04.000
This is the bottom left square

09:04.000 --> 09:07.000
It is considered the most ineffective

09:07.000 --> 09:09.000
It is considered the cold zone of the store

09:09.000 --> 09:12.000
If your product is located in this zone, do not be surprised

09:12.000 --> 09:14.000
Why are your sales so small

09:14.000 --> 09:17.000
How to avoid this

09:17.000 --> 09:19.000
You can highlight something bright

09:19.000 --> 09:21.000
You can put large figures

09:21.000 --> 09:23.000
Additional lighting

09:23.000 --> 09:27.000
Any bright things that attract the attention of the buyer

09:27.000 --> 09:29.000
And will make them go further

09:29.000 --> 09:31.000
Remember the location of the supermarkets

09:31.000 --> 09:34.000
In this department, most often, there is bread

09:34.000 --> 09:36.000
And not only is it baked there

09:36.000 --> 09:40.000
The smell of bread makes us go there

09:40.000 --> 09:43.000
Like Pavlov's dog, this smell

09:43.000 --> 09:45.000
Makes us go through most of the store

09:45.000 --> 09:49.000
That is why departments are placed in this way

09:49.000 --> 09:54.000
Also on the slide you have the rules of the golden triangle

09:54.000 --> 10:00.000
The location of the golden triangle consists of three parts

10:00.000 --> 10:02.000
The first is the entrance

10:02.000 --> 10:04.000
The second point is the checkout

10:04.000 --> 10:07.000
And the third point is the departments that are visited most often

10:07.000 --> 10:08.000
By the buyer

10:08.000 --> 10:09.000
Milk, meat

10:09.000 --> 10:13.000
That is, daily products are sold there

10:13.000 --> 10:17.000
For which the buyer came for sure

10:17.000 --> 10:21.000
And your task as a manufacturer

10:21.000 --> 10:24.000
If you are a manufacturer, to get into the zone of this golden triangle

10:24.000 --> 10:27.000
Because when you get into the zone of the golden triangle

10:27.000 --> 10:30.000
Your sales increase by at least 80%

10:30.000 --> 10:33.000
There, most often, the buyers pass

10:33.000 --> 10:36.000
And the task of the store itself is to expand this zone

10:36.000 --> 10:41.000
That is, to distribute the most popular departments, checkout and entrance by distance

10:41.000 --> 10:46.000
Thus, expanding the field of active activity of buyers

10:46.000 --> 10:48.000
And the zone of active purchases

10:48.000 --> 10:53.000
Well, we move on to stimulating end consumers

10:53.000 --> 10:58.000
Not all companies are engaged in stimulating end consumers

10:58.000 --> 11:03.000
Nevertheless, yes, it is an expensive process, but very necessary

11:03.000 --> 11:06.000
Because the client can leave us to other intermediaries

11:06.000 --> 11:08.000
If he is not satisfied with our discount

11:08.000 --> 11:10.000
And end consumers are more loyal

11:10.000 --> 11:12.000
If they liked our products

11:12.000 --> 11:15.000
They will definitely come back to us

11:15.000 --> 11:20.000
Buying from us and providing us with this or that income

11:20.000 --> 11:25.000
So, when we stimulate end consumers

11:25.000 --> 11:28.000
The main goal is, of course, to increase the volume of sales

11:28.000 --> 11:31.000
But you can increase the volume of sales in several ways

11:31.000 --> 11:35.000
And you have it shown on the diagram

11:35.000 --> 11:39.000
At least, the increase in sales is divided into two parts

11:39.000 --> 11:42.000
To ensure loyalty and trial purchases

11:42.000 --> 11:45.000
Trial purchases are, of course, more related to the new product

11:45.000 --> 11:48.000
And loyalty is already related to the existing product

11:48.000 --> 11:52.000
To maintain the recognition and loyalty of our product

11:52.000 --> 11:55.000
These two groups are divided into goals

11:55.000 --> 11:59.000
Additionally, trial purchases are divided into two parts

11:59.000 --> 12:03.000
Pre-ordering of the product, that is, the person should want to buy it

12:03.000 --> 12:07.000
And availability, he should find a place where it is sold

12:07.000 --> 12:11.000
And loyalty is divided into three parts

12:11.000 --> 12:13.000
Frequency of purchase, how often do they buy

12:13.000 --> 12:16.000
Adherence, do they buy our brand all the time

12:17.000 --> 12:22.000
And the possibility or frequency of switching from the brand of competitors to our brand

12:22.000 --> 12:28.000
All these five goals are laid out further

12:28.000 --> 12:31.000
You can see it in the lecture material

12:31.000 --> 12:37.000
There is a detailed description of each of the possible goals

12:37.000 --> 12:44.000
When setting and developing the stimulation program for end consumers

12:44.000 --> 12:48.000
We will see how to properly plan these actions

12:48.000 --> 12:53.000
Planning consists of three main steps

12:53.000 --> 12:55.000
The first is to determine the target audience

12:55.000 --> 12:59.000
We must understand who we are targeting our program for

12:59.000 --> 13:01.000
Who are its participants

13:01.000 --> 13:06.000
There are several criteria that help the target audience to determine the end consumers

13:06.000 --> 13:10.000
Three main groups are regional criteria

13:10.000 --> 13:13.000
The lifestyle of consumers

13:13.000 --> 13:16.000
And the third group is demographic criteria

13:16.000 --> 13:23.000
I will tell you that demographic criteria are most often used

13:23.000 --> 13:28.000
Age, gender, education level

13:28.000 --> 13:34.000
The second place is regional criteria, location, climate

13:34.000 --> 13:36.000
It is very important for some products

13:36.000 --> 13:41.000
And the third place is the criteria of the lifestyle of consumers

13:41.000 --> 13:45.000
These criteria are more sociological, that's why they are used less often

13:45.000 --> 13:49.000
To determine your target audience by these criteria

13:49.000 --> 13:53.000
You need specialists, sociologists or psychologists

13:53.000 --> 13:55.000
That's why they are used less often

13:55.000 --> 13:58.000
When we determined the target audience, we described it

13:58.000 --> 14:02.000
For example, our target audience of vitamins

14:02.000 --> 14:04.000
Polyvitamins

14:04.000 --> 14:10.000
These are women between 25 and 45 years old

14:10.000 --> 14:15.000
With a family, at least one child

14:15.000 --> 14:26.000
Working, with a higher or lower education

14:27.000 --> 14:34.000
Living in cities with a population of at least 200,000 people

14:34.000 --> 14:38.000
Here is a segmentation of vitamins consumption

14:38.000 --> 14:43.000
Of course, all other categories, women or men, can also consume vitamins

14:43.000 --> 14:46.000
But we, remember, select the target audience

14:46.000 --> 14:50.000
That is, the one that buys the most

14:50.000 --> 14:52.000
Here we have determined it

14:52.000 --> 14:57.000
The clearer your segmentation, the more competently you will develop the promotion program

14:57.000 --> 15:05.000
Remember, skeletons are yogurts that were aimed at a group of teenagers between 12 and 14 years old

15:05.000 --> 15:08.000
The positioning was very clear

15:08.000 --> 15:12.000
It was this that gave such success to this product

15:12.000 --> 15:16.000
Yes, parents didn't like this product because there were skeletons drawn

15:16.000 --> 15:18.000
It was ridiculous and funny

15:18.000 --> 15:21.000
Or maybe it was unpleasant for someone

15:21.000 --> 15:24.000
But skeletons achieved their target audience

15:24.000 --> 15:27.000
And their sales were amazing

15:27.000 --> 15:34.000
Therefore, the target audience is a determining factor of success

15:34.000 --> 15:37.000
The second step is the time of holding

15:37.000 --> 15:41.000
We determine how long the promotion will last

15:41.000 --> 15:43.000
It can be a long-term promotion

15:43.000 --> 15:46.000
It can be held during the season

15:46.000 --> 15:49.000
Or regular events, or periodic

15:49.000 --> 15:51.000
What is it about?

15:51.000 --> 15:53.000
Or some festive events

15:53.000 --> 16:01.000
And we determine whether it is short-term, medium-term, and long-term

16:01.000 --> 16:03.000
It can be more than 3 months and up to a year

16:03.000 --> 16:08.000
Although I will say that short-term events are more effective than long-term

16:08.000 --> 16:09.000
Why?

16:09.000 --> 16:13.000
When we hold a promotion program in a short period

16:13.000 --> 16:15.000
The effect comes quickly

16:15.000 --> 16:17.000
Sales rise quickly

16:17.000 --> 16:20.000
And we see the result right away

16:20.000 --> 16:24.000
Because we make our customers act immediately

16:24.000 --> 16:26.000
The duration of the action is limited by the program

16:26.000 --> 16:31.000
And when the program is long-term, there is such a postponement effect

16:31.000 --> 16:33.000
The program is still going on for a long time

16:33.000 --> 16:36.000
I will come later, I will do it later, I will buy it later

16:36.000 --> 16:38.000
While I have this, while I have that

16:38.000 --> 16:40.000
As a result, your promotion works worse

16:40.000 --> 16:42.000
It has no peak

16:42.000 --> 16:45.000
It rises a little and goes to this level

16:45.000 --> 16:51.000
And you get the feeling that you spend a lot, but you have no effect

16:51.000 --> 16:57.000
Therefore, short-term promotions work more effectively

16:57.000 --> 17:01.000
And work more purposefully for end consumers

17:01.000 --> 17:06.000
Well, the third point that we must determine is budget restrictions

17:06.000 --> 17:10.000
The budget is offered in different ways

17:10.000 --> 17:12.000
It is developed in different ways

17:12.000 --> 17:15.000
Here are the main methods of budget formation

17:15.000 --> 17:17.000
The first is the percentage of sales

17:17.000 --> 17:22.000
When we say that we have a sales volume and such a percentage, for example, 3 or 5 percent

17:22.000 --> 17:25.000
We can take it for a promotion program

17:25.000 --> 17:29.000
Yes, this is an option, because it depends on the turnover, it is tied clearly

17:29.000 --> 17:32.000
And we will not spend more than necessary

17:32.000 --> 17:34.000
The second option is possible, it is from the profit

17:34.000 --> 17:38.000
The owner says, wow, you can take from the turnover

17:38.000 --> 17:42.000
And you take from the additional turnover, how much you earn additionally, or rather from the profit

17:42.000 --> 17:48.000
This is also a correct option, because it is important for the owner how much additional money he will receive

17:48.000 --> 17:53.000
And not just stimulate his end consumers

17:53.000 --> 17:56.000
The next point is planning for goals

17:56.000 --> 18:00.000
When you set goals, determine the share that you need

18:00.000 --> 18:02.000
And then you form a budget

18:02.000 --> 18:04.000
And then you approve this budget

18:04.000 --> 18:07.000
Planning for goals is the most competent option for planning

18:07.000 --> 18:10.000
But, of course, you need to calculate and not go into losses

18:10.000 --> 18:16.000
If we planned for goals that we need to spend certain amounts

18:16.000 --> 18:20.000
It does not mean that the company should work in losses

18:20.000 --> 18:23.000
The marketer should count both sides of the coin

18:23.000 --> 18:26.000
Both sides of the spending and sides of the income

18:26.000 --> 18:31.000
Otherwise, the share will not be effective, and therefore it will not be a stimulus share

18:31.000 --> 18:35.000
The next two points that can be taken into account

